main event: Air Force pilots observed an unidentified object leaving a contrail over Clark Air Force Base in the Philippines on September 8, 1949.
interesting points: The object was climbing at a steep angle and traveling at a high speed, estimated to exceed 800 mph,Multiple witnesses could only see the contrail and not the object itself,The object climbed to altitudes between 40,000 and 50,000 feet before leveling off,Two F-51s were in the area but the con-trail was thought to belong to an unidentified object,The observed contrail remained visible for some time before it dissipated.
sighted object: unidentified high-speed object leaving a contrail
witness description: Air Force pilots from the 67th Fighter Squadron
